{"title": "Your Door Was Open", "content": "A common situation in a TV show with limited time to show events, where a character will suddenly appear in another character's home with no explanation. It can be interpreted as merely a shorthand to indicate that the character has in fact knocked and been let in but the scene is too boring to air. However, the trope often appears in contexts where that should not be possible, like when the person entering the house walks in on someone's private affairs, or is a villain, or is out of favor with the resident and walks in just to berate him, etc. Why nobody ever, at the very least, locks their door when they want to be alone is a great mystery.\n\nNot to be confused with There Was a Door.\n\nThe Drop-In Character does this all the time.\n\nSee also: Swiss Cheese Security, Trespassing to Talk, and Interrupted Intimacy.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourDoorWasOpen", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Coupling", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Kannagi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/ToLoveRu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DailyLifeWithMonsterGirl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/NeonGenesisEvangelion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Watchmen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheSimpsons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MaiHime", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/KatawaShoujo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/NotAnotherTeenMovie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheJetsons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheKidsGuideToTheInternet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RearWindow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheOutsiders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LittleWomen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/IDreamOfJeannie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BabylonFive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheFlash2014", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Friends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Coupling", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Friends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.ph